{"abstract":[{"text":"In Lion, we revisit the basics of how views are placed in windows for the first time since Mac OS X 10.0. Springs and struts (i.e. autoresizing masks) are out, dashed blue Interface Builder guides are in. Rather than being one-off helpers for setting a frame in IB, guides become persistent objects that maintain a relationship at runtime. Come see what’s going on, and what merited such a big change.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11-103-Cocoa-Autolayout","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2011\/103\/"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC11","title":"Cocoa Autolayout"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc11-103-cocoa-autolayout"]}],"references":{"WWDC11.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC11.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documen